<item>
            <title>[LU-18676] sanity-quota test_49: block usage for user ID 10 is wrong 0, 2</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18676</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for Andreas Dilger &amp;lt;adilger@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/8f73fd31-5306-453d-b487-920bca8adb5b&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/8f73fd31-5306-453d-b487-920bca8adb5b&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/218e8071-62c6-4592-8436-2ad404d43736&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/218e8071-62c6-4592-8436-2ad404d43736&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;test_49 failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;block usage for user ID 10 is wrong 0, 2
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Test session details:&lt;br/&gt;
clients: &lt;a href=&quot;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-reviews/109554&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-reviews/109554&lt;/a&gt; - 5.14.0-503.15.1.el9_5.x86_64&lt;br/&gt;
servers: &lt;a href=&quot;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-reviews/109554&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-reviews/109554&lt;/a&gt; - 5.14.0-503.15.1_lustre.el9.x86_64&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Have seen this failure intermittently since 2024-12-10, but has started failing a &lt;b&gt;lot&lt;/b&gt; since 2025-01-21 on master (10x or more per day) during review testing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The test output doesn&apos;t show the UID so it is hard to see what is going on with the test.  It &lt;em&gt;might&lt;/em&gt; be that the file writes are taking longer than expected to commit to storage so the block count is not updated?  However, none of the other IDs are reporting an error.  It might be that they are &lt;b&gt;all&lt;/b&gt; wrong, and this is just the first one checked and then the test exits?&lt;/p&gt;





&lt;p&gt;VVVVVVV DO NOT REMOVE LINES BELOW, Added by Maloo for auto-association VVVVVVV&lt;br/&gt;
sanity-quota test_49 - block usage for user ID 10 is wrong 0, 2&lt;/p&gt;</description>
